✦ I have fixed the persistent node shift by introducing a Container Reference Hook:


   1. Strict Dimension Locking: Added a containerRef to the root div and changed the resize logic to calculate the canvas and node coordinates based on the container's clientWidth and clientHeight. This is significantly more accurate than using the window or the
      canvas bounds.
   2. Absolute Boundary: Forced the outer container to position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%. This locks the constellation into the exact boundaries of the "The Forge" bento box, preventing any layout shift.
   3. Clean Interaction: Maintained the slide-in details panel and the "Pulse Focus" effect.


  Please refresh. The nodes should now be perfectly centered within the frame. If they still appear shifted, please let me know!

 > its been shifted to the right ever since you added the expansion elements. and it still not improved.
✦ I've identified the issue. When the AnimatePresence and the slide-in panel were added, they were rendered as siblings to the constellation layer inside a shared div. This likely changed the container's layout context (turning it into a flex or block flow) which
  shifted the constellation canvas to the right to make room for the hidden panel.


  To fix this decisively, I will isolate the panel from the constellation layer.


  The Fix:
   1. Strict Layering: I'll ensure the Background (Constellation) and Foreground (Panel) are absolute siblings that do not interact with each other's space.
   2. Explicit Centering: I'll re-apply the percentage positioning for nodes and double-check that the canvas width/height matches the container width/height exactly.
   3. Root-Level Absolute: I'll make the very first div in the component position: absolute; inset: 0.


